ppened...He%20felt%20that%20if%20I%20am%20not%20needed%20right%20now%20in%20the%20series%2C%20I%20am%20better%20off%20saying%20goodbye%20to%20the%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20India%20captain%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20when%20a%20player%20like%20him%20who%20has%20had%20so%20many%20moments%20with%20the%20Indian%20team%20and%20he%20has%20been%20a%20truly%20big%20match-winner%20for%20us%2C%20he%20is%20allowed%20to%20make%20those%20decisions%20on%20his%20own%20and%20if%20it%20was%20now%2C%20so%20be%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Rohit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin's%20predecessor%20Harbhajan%20Singh%20felt%20the%20Chennai-man%20could%20have%20delayed%20this%20announcement%20until%20after%20the%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNumbers%20can't%20lie%20and%20he%20has%20such%20a%20phenomenal%20record.%20I%20would%20have%20ideally%20liked%20him%20to%20stay%20back%20for%20the%20final%20two%20Tests%20as%20in%20Sydney%2C%20he%20could%20have%20played%20a%20part.%20But%20it's%20an%20individual%20call%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20name%20is%20as%20big%20as%20Ashwin%2C%20it%20is%20the%20player%2C%20who%20decides.%20May%20be%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20hang%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20'Turbantor'%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20school%20of%20thought%20that%20even%20if%20India%20would%20have%20gone%20with%20two%20spinners%20in%20Sydney%20if%20the%20conditions%20permitted%2C%20Jadeja%20would%20have%20been%20paired%20with%20Washington%2C%20because%20both%20are%20considered%20more%20capable%20batters%20in%20SENA%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahendra%20Singh%20Dhoni%20had%20announced%20his%20decision%20to%20retire%20from%20Test%20cricket%20after%20the%20third%20game%20in%20Melbourne%20but%20that%20had%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20long%20sessions%20of%20keeping%20which%20were%20affecting%20his%20dodgy%20back%20and%20he%20desperately%20wanted%20to%20continue%20playing%20white-ball%20cricket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20Ashwin%2C%20the%20realisation%20that%20he%20is%20not%20even%20being%20considered%20among%20the%20top%20two%20spinners%20must%20have%20been%20too%20much%20to%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734518040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fda7qejlo_ashwin_625x300_18_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Faustralia-vs-india-2024-25%2Fno-chat-with-bcci-report-reveals-r-ashwins-retirement-mayve-been-hastened-by-this-players-selection-7276958%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20played%20Washington%20Sundar%20ahead%20of%20Ashwin%20in%20Perth%20before%20the%20veteran%20returned%20for%20the%20pink%20ball%20Test%2C%20at%20Rohit's%20insistence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%2011%20Reasons%20Simultaneous%20Elections%20Aren't%20'Anti-Constitution'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-03%2Fqeklno2_voting-generic-up-pti-650_650x400_07_March_22.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20brief%20debate%20on%20December%2017%2C%202024%2C%20Law%20Minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20introduced%20the%20129th%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%20Bill%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20institute%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20both%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20State%20Assemblies%2C%20was%20put%20to%20a%20division%20of%20votes%20at%20the%20insistence%20of%20Opposition%20members%2C%20ultimately%20passing%20with%20269%20votes%20in%20support%20and%20198%20in%20opposition.%20It%20has%20now%20been%20referred%20to%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%20for%20closer%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Opposition%20MPs%20argued%20that%20holding%20concurrent%20elections%20would%20infringe%20upon%20the%20Constitution's%20basic%20structure.%20The%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20in%20its%20submission%20to%20the%20High-Level%20Committee%20(HLC)%20on%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%20claimed%20that%20such%20a%20reform%20would%20bring%20about%20%E2%80%9Csubstantial%20changes%20to%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20similarly%20contended%20that%20simultaneous%20elections%20would%20weaken%20democracy%2C%20a%20core%20constitutional%20value.%20Echoing%20these%20sentiments%2C%20many%20Opposition%20leaders%20called%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9Canti-federal%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20despite%20these%20allegations%2C%20the%20Bill%20does%20not%20contravene%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine.%20In%20fact%2C%20there%20are%2010%20compelling%20reasons%20why%20it%20remains%20consistent%20with%20the%20Constitution's%20foundational%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitution%20Allows%20Flexibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20simultaneous%20elections%20were%20a%20norm%20in%20the%20early%20years%20of%20the%20Republic%20(1951-52%2C%201957%2C%201962%2C%20and%201967)%20without%20any%20adverse%20impact%20on%20the%20constitutional%20framework%20or%20democratic%20ethos.%20The%20continuation%20of%20a%20constitutionally%20sanctioned%20practice%20cannot%20be%20deemed%20to%20violate%20the%20basic%20structure.%20No%20judicial%20pronouncement%20has%20held%20that%20the%20earlier%20practice%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20was%20unconstitutional%20or%20detrimental%20to%20the%20Constitution's%20core%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20it%20is%20often%20argued%20that%20simultaneous%20elections%20run%20afoul%20of%20the%20Constitution's%20basic%20structure%20because%20they%20may%20necessitate%20the%20early%20dissolution%20of%20State%20Legislative%20Assemblies%E2%80%94bodies%20composed%20of%20elected%20representatives%E2%80%94thereby%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20going%20against%20the%20people's%20expressed%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20report%20by%20the%20HLC%20has%20argued%2C%20the%20Constitution%20itself%20contemplates%20that%20the%20duration%20of%20both%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20and%20the%20Legislative%20Assemblies%20shall%20be%20%E2%80%9Cfive%20years%20unless%20dissolved%20sooner%E2%80%9D.%20This%20formulation%20highlights%20that%20the%20framers%20consciously%20introduced%20flexibility%20into%20legislative%20tenures.%20Since%20premature%20dissolution%20is%20already%20constitutionally%20sanctioned%2C%20its%20calibrated%20use%20to%20achieve%20synchronised%20election%20cycles%20does%20not%20introduce%20any%20fundamentally%20new%20or%20prohibited%20element%20into%20the%20constitutional%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Threat%20To%20Basic%20Structure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20essential%20features%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%E2%80%94such%20as%20the%20trilogy%20of%20rights%20(Articles%2014%2C%2019%2C%20and%2021)%2C%20fundamental%20freedoms%2C%20the%20balance%20between%20Parts%20III%20and%20IV%2C%20secularism%2C%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%E2%80%94remain%20untouched.%20The%20HLC%20report%20explicitly%20states%20that%20the%20criticisms%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20not%20impinge%20upon%20citizens%20rights%20under%20Part%20III%20or%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20or%20any%20other%20features%20such%20as%20a%20free%20and%20independent%20judiciary%E2%80%9D.%20Therefore%2C%20no%20core%20constitutional%20value%20recognised%20in%20%3Cem%3EKesavananda%20Bharati%20v.%20State%20of%20Kerala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(AIR%201973%20SC%201461)%20is%20impaired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20democracy%2C%20recognised%20as%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20(%3Cem%3EKesavananda%20Bharati%20v.%20State%20of%20Kerala%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201973%20SC%201461%3B%20Kihoto%20Hollohan%20v.%20Zachilhu%2C%20AIR%201993%20SC%20412)%2C%20is%20not%20jeopardised%20by%20holding%20elections%20together.%20Periodic%2C%20free%2C%20and%20fair%20elections%20remain%20intact.%20The%20proposed%20amendment%20does%20not%20curtail%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20vote%20or%20their%20ability%20to%20choose%20representatives.%20It%20merely%20synchronises%20election%20timings%2C%20ensuring%20the%20democratic%20principle%20of%20periodic%20electoral%20endorsement%20is%20fully%20preserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20affirmed%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20as%20integral%20to%20democracy%20and%20hence%20to%20the%20basic%20structure%20(%3Cem%3EIndira%20Nehru%20Gandhi%20v.%20Raj%20Narain%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201975%20SC%202299%3B%20%3Cem%3EUnion%20of%20India%20v.%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%202002%20SC%202112).%20The%20proposed%20amendment%20does%20not%20amend%20the%20powers%2C%20functions%2C%20or%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20dilute%20judicial%20review%20mechanisms.%20Hence%2C%20the%20fairness%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20remain%20unimpaired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESix%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20while%20democracy%20is%20fundamental%2C%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20and%20the%20right%20to%20contest%20are%20not%20fundamental%20rights%3B%20they%20are%20constitutional%20and%20statutory%20rights%20(%3Cem%3EN.P.%20Ponnuswami%20v.%20Returning%20Officer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201952%20SC%2064%3B%20%3Cem%3EKuldip%20Nayar%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%202006%20SC%203127).%20Aligning%20elections%20does%20not%20restrict%20or%20remove%20these%20rights%3B%20it%20merely%20adjusts%20their%20timing.%20No%20provision%20of%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20converts%20these%20rights%20into%20something%20constitutionally%20impermissible%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20interfere%20with%20their%20statutory%20framework.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitution%20Is%20Still%20Supreme%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeven%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20federalism%2C%20though%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%2C%20is%20not%20absolute%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%20Indian%20federalism%20is%20%3Cem%3Esui%20generis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%E2%80%9Cquasi-federal%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccooperative%20federalism%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3ES.R.%20Bommai%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201994%20SC%201918%3B%20%3Cem%3EGovernment%20of%20NCT%20of%20Delhi%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20(2018)%208%20SCALE%2072).%20The%20proposed%20amendment%20does%20not%20alter%20the%20distribution%20of%20legislative%20or%20executive%20powers.%20It%20does%20not%20affect%20the%20competence%20of%20States%2C%20their%20legislative%20autonomy%2C%20or%20the%20constitutional%20status%20of%20the%20Union-State%20relationship.%20Rather%2C%20it%20preserves%20the%20federal%20balance%20while%20enhancing%20administrative%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEight%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20judicial%20review%E2%80%94core%20features%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20(%3Cem%3EMinerva%20Mills%20Ltd.%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201980%20SC%201789)%E2%80%94are%20neither%20suspended%20nor%20diluted%20by%20the%20proposed%20amendment.%20Courts%20retain%20their%20full%20authority%20to%20strike%20down%20unconstitutional%20acts.%20The%20amendment%20only%20reorganises%20electoral%20timetables%20and%20does%20not%20immunise%20any%20measure%20from%20judicial%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20secularism%2C%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20and%20separation%20of%20powers%E2%80%94hallmarks%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%E2%80%94remain%20intact%20(%3Cem%3ES.R.%20Bommai%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201994%20SC%201918%3B%20%3Cem%3EM.%20Nagaraj%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%202007%20SC%2071).%20The%20amendment%20does%20not%20impinge%20upon%20the%20authority%20of%20Parliament%2C%20State%20Legislatures%2C%20or%20the%20judiciary.%20It%20does%20not%20alter%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20governance%20but%20merely%20standardises%20the%20electoral%20calendar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20for%20a%20violation%20of%20basic%20structure%20to%20occur%2C%20the%20constitutional%20identity%20itself%20must%20be%20threatened%20or%20altered%20(%3Cem%3EI.R.%20Coelho%20v.%20State%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%202007%20SC%20861).%20Synchronising%20elections%20neither%20changes%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20Constitution%20as%20a%20democratic%2C%20republican%2C%20and%20federal%20polity%20nor%20introduces%20any%20new%20constitutional%20element%20that%20is%20repugnant%20to%20the%20existing%20constitutional%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEleven%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20objective%20behind%20simultaneous%20elections%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20electoral%20management%20rather%20than%20constitutional%20restructuring.%20Such%20efficiency%20measures%20do%20not%20dismantle%20the%20foundational%20pillars%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20clarified%20that%20what%20is%20proscribed%20is%20the%20destruction%20or%20emasculation%20of%20the%20Constitution's%20core%20features%2C%20not%20procedural%20or%20administrative%20reforms%20consistent%20with%20its%20principles%20(%3Cem%3ESajjan%20Singh%20v.%20State%20of%20Rajasthan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20AIR%201965%20SC%20845).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BMisplaced%26quot%3B%20Criticisms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20to%20synchronise%20electoral%20cycles%2C%20aimed%20at%20minimising%20the%20frequency%20of%20elections%2C%20reducing%20administrative%20costs%2C%20and%20mitigating%20the%20repeated%20invocation%20of%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%2C%20finds%20support%20among%20eminent%20jurists%2C%20thereby%20reinforcing%20its%20constitutional%20propriety.%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%2C%20in%20his%20letter%20dated%20February%2028%2C%202024%2C%20to%20the%20HLC%2C%20opined%20that%20criticisms%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20as%20antithetical%20to%20the%20basic%20structure%20or%20federal%20principles%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmisplaced%E2%80%9D.%20He%20invoked%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdoctrine%20of%20expansion%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdoctrine%20of%20reduction%E2%80%9D%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20constitutional%20flexibility%20to%20extend%20or%20curtail%20legislative%20tenures%20in%20exceptional%20circumstances%2C%20underscoring%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20being%20quasi-federal%2C%20simultaneous%20elections%20for%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20and%20State%20Legislative%20Assemblies%20are%20not%20anti-federal%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20elucidating%20the%20benefits%2C%20Justice%20Misra%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9Csynchronising%20elections%20at%20the%20National%20and%20State%20levels%20could%20lead%20to%20greater%20administrative%20efficiency%20by%20reducing%20the%20frequency%20of%20elections%20and%20associated%20costs%E2%80%9D.%20He%20observed%20that%20this%20measure%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20benefit%20both%20the%20Central%20Government%20and%20State%20Governments%E2%80%9D%20and%20enhance%20governance%20by%20enabling%20representatives%20to%20dedicate%20greater%20attention%20to%20legislative%20and%20executive%20functions%2C%20free%20from%20the%20interruptions%20of%20staggered%20elections.%20He%20explicitly%20concluded%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cadoption%20of%20One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%20in%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20brook%20well%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20also%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20collaborative%20federalism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitics%20Over%20Reforms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Opposition's%20objections%20to%20simultaneous%20elections%20appear%20to%20be%20driven%20more%20by%20political%20expediency%20than%20constitutional%20merit%2C%20the%20arguments%20they%20present%20fail%20to%20withstand%20legal%20scrutiny.%20The%20framers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20envisaged%20a%20flexible%20framework%20for%20legislative%20terms%2C%20and%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20merely%20harmonises%20this%20flexibility%20to%20achieve%20stability%20and%20efficiency%20in%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20aptly%20remarked%2C%20simultaneous%20elections%20neither%20undermine%20federalism%20nor%20violate%20the%20Constitution's%20basic%20structure%3B%20rather%2C%20they%20%E2%80%9Cbrook%20well%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D%20and%20embody%20the%20principles%20of%20collaborative%20federalism.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%20opposition's%20insistence%20on%20clinging%20to%20staggered%20elections%20reflects%20a%20misplaced%20reluctance%20to%20embrace%20reforms%20that%20prioritise%20governance%20over%20perpetual%20politicking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20a%20public%20policy%20professional%20and%20an%20author.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734517560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-03%2Fqeklno2_voting-generic-up-pti-650_650x400_07_March_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2F11-reasons-simultaneous-elections-arent-anti-constitution-7276861%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20Oppositions%20objections%20to%20simultaneous%20elections%20appear%20to%20be%20driven%20more%20by%20political%20expediency%20than%2